description|core_description|display_no: adapter to connect audio source to replay device via 3.5mm male aux audio lead
detailed description|text|display_no: this item is used to play sound from audio sources like mp3-players, cd-players or similar on devices with no input (e.g. bluetooth, aux-in) availability.
usage|text|display_no: the cassette part was placed inside a replay device with cassette holder (autoradio, cassette recorder, tapedeck) and the 3.5mm lead plugged into the sound source device (e.g. mp3-player). pressing play on the cassette holding device and if necessary selecting :tape: as sound source on this device played the sound from the source connected with to the plug.
